This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the understanding of sarcasm in natural language. Additionally, the use of neural models and attention mechanisms suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's focus on social communities such as Twitter and Reddit suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of figurative language and contrastive themes may also relate to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
